cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a deep learning architecture for predicting depth from a video sequence, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also incorporates elements of classical Structure from Motion, which involves geometric reasoning and optimization, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses multi-scale 3D convolutional networks, which are commonly used in graphics (cs.GR) research.
